CoCanvas
========

CoCanvas is a local-first collaborative canvas for reviewing Markdown and HTML
documents with an AI agent.

Attribution
-----------

CoCanvas began as a fork of Roughdraft, the local-first Markdown review app
built by Nathan Baschez at Lex Inc. and released under the MIT license.

  Upstream project: https://github.com/Lex-Inc/roughdraft
  Author:           Nathan Baschez (https://twitter.com/nbashaw)

Substantial portions of CoCanvas — including the Roughdraft Flavored Markdown
specification, the CriticMarkup parser, the local server CLI, and the review
UI — derive from that original work. The original copyright and MIT license
text are reproduced in LICENSE.

CoCanvas extends the original with experimental HTML review support, including
the HTML annotation contract recorded in
`docs/adr/0005-html-review-annotation-contract.md`, the corresponding MCP
tools, and related editor changes. New work on top of Roughdraft is also
released under the MIT license.

Internal package names
----------------------

CoCanvas keeps the original `@roughdraft/*` workspace package names
(`@roughdraft/app`, `@roughdraft/server`, `@roughdraft/rfm`, `@roughdraft/skill`)
to minimise churn against the upstream history. The `cocanvas` CLI binary is
the primary entry point; a `roughdraft` alias is preserved for compatibility
with existing scripts and agent instructions.
